HEADWORD: Galimatias
<hw>Gal`i*ma"tias</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>Nonsense; gibberish; confused and unmeaning talk; confused
mixture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her dress, like her talk, is a <qex>galimatias</qex> of several
countries.</q> <rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Galingale</ent>⟦br⟧
